I'm working on a web application using JavaScript and I can't figure out why my async function isn't waiting for the promise to resolve. It's supposed to fetch data from an API and then process it, but it seems to skip the waiting part. My code is as follows: async function fetchData() {
    let response = fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
    let data = response.json();
    console.log(data);
}
fetchData();

reference_answer:
The issue here is that you're not using 'await' with the 'fetch' function and the 'json()' method. Both these operations return promises and need to be awaited in an async function. The corrected code should look like this: async function fetchData() {
    let response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
    let data = await response.json();
    console.log(data);
}
fetchData(); 

This modification will ensure that the function waits for the data to be fetched and processed before logging it to the console.
